{
  "texts": [
    "c) Fully Connected Layers: Feature maps generated from convolution and pooling layers are flattened to be fed to fully connected layers.",
    "They connect every neuron in the current layer to every other neuron in the next layer.",
    "In applying CNN for HSI classification, 2D-CNN has displayed wide applicability in extracting spatial features (Yu et al., 2017).",
    "Due to redundancy in the hyperspectral cube, the convolution kernel size tends to enlarge.",
    "This limitation was removed by using a combination of 1D convolution and 2D convolution."
  ]
}